Date: Thu, 29 Jan 1998 05:11:51 -0500 (EST)
From: Chwan-Chuen King <a1234567@ccms.ntu.edu.tw>

We also used mouse brain killed JE vaccine with 3 shots. You can review
our publication in J. Med. Virol 44(2):122 by Ku et al (l994). We found
that Beijing strain was better than Nakayama for Chinese children living in
city, rural area and isolated islands. Regarding the JE vaccine in China,
Dr. Tsai and Dr. Jeff Chang at CDC know more about [this. If you have
further questions, please contact them.
Happy New Year of the Tiger.
--
Chwan-Chuen King, Dr.P.H.
Professor, Epidemiology of Infectious Disease
College of Public Health
National Taiwan University
FAX:8862-2351-1955
