e-mail: a1234567@ccms.ntu.edu.tw
[Ted Tsai (DVBID, CDC, Fort Collins replied: "The vaccine mentioned by
Henry Wilde is the live attenuated SA14-14-2 JE vaccine developed and
produced in China. The involvement of US researchers, mainly through Scott
Halstead's efforts, has been to perform further evaluations of safety,
effectiveness and immunogenicity - essentially to validate the published
Chinese results with more fully characterized studies. It clearly is a
safe and effective vaccine; however, it is produced and available only in
China. A Korean company is seeking licensure of the vaccine in Korea with
hopes of distributing it there and, potentially, internationally; however,
it is unclear when that approval process will be completed. As far as cost
is concerned, the vaccine's cost is government subsidized in China so,
although I've been quoted a cost of 3 cents per dose for public health
programs in China, the real cost, if the vaccine were to be produced in a
free market system under internationally acceptable standards, is bound to
be higher. Please see "Vaccines" - edited by Plotkin and Mortimer. I
wrote the JE vaccine chapter. The third edition of the book is in press."
Thanks to Ted for this knowledgeable response.
Thanks also to C.C. for her input but I must correct one small assumption.
It may be the Year of the Tiger in China but it is the Year of the Bronco
in Colorado (and Green Bay). - Mod.CHC
